consider the problem of finding their numerical solutions by using a recent characterization theorem of Bede for fuzzy differential equations. We prove a corollary to Bede's characterization theorem and give a characterization theorem for hybrid fuzzy differential equation IVPs. Then we prove that any suitable numerical method for ODEs can be applied piecewise to numerically solve hybrid fuzzy differential equation IVPs. Numerical examples are provided which connect the new results with previous findings.", :doc-id "Numerical solution of hybrid fuzzy differential equation IVPs by a characterization theorem. 2009  ,  "}, 3146147 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 3146147, :key "journals/jcam/FerreiraFMPY11", :title "Analytical and numerical treatment of oscillatory mixed differential equations with differentiable delays and advances.", :abstract nil, :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 1584367, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "José M. Ferreira"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 136866, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Neville J. Ford"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 14144373, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Md. Abdul Malique"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 1196264, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Sandra Pinelas"} #search_api.search_api.Author{:id 878185, :first-name nil, :last-name nil, :full-name "Yubin Yan"}), :year 2011, :venue "J. Computational Applied Mathematics", :ncit 0, :string "Analytical and numerical treatment of oscillatory mixed differential equations with differentiable delays and advances.. ", :doc-id "Analytical and numerical treatment of oscillatory mixed differential equations with differentiable delays and advances. 2011  ,  ,  ,  ,  "}, 3191427 #search_api.search_api.Paper{:id 3191427, :key "conf/synasc/NegreaH10", :title "Numerical Solutions for a Class of Backward Stochastic Differential Equations.", :abstract nil, :author (#search_api.search_api.Author{:id 383917, :first-name nil, 